cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper is about compressing convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for machine vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the performance of different compression schemes, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG - Machine Learning). The algorithm used for pruning filters is based on a greedy approach, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI - Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the reduction in size of the network, which is related to neural networks (cs.NE - Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the interpretability of the compressed CNNs, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM - Multimedia).
